<paragraphs>
    <title>A Basic Triangle Problem</title>
<p>
     Using the triangle given below, find each of the insicated values.  
</p>
<sidebyside>
<image>   
<prefigure label = "right-triangle-problem" xmlns="https://prefigure.org">
<diagram dimensions="(300,300)" margins="(50,5,50,5)">
  <coordinates bbox="(-2,-2,12,10)">
    <definition>points=((10,0),(0,0),(10,5))</definition>
    <triangle vertices="points"
              angle-markers="yes"/>
    <angle-marker points="points" radius="30">
      <m>\theta</m>
    </angle-marker>
    <label anchor="(5,0)" alignment="south">
      <m>10</m>
    </label>
    <label anchor="(10,2.5)" alignment="east">
      <m>5</m>
    </label>
    <label anchor="(9,4.25)" alignment="south">
      <m>\phi</m>
    </label>
  </coordinates>
</diagram>
</prefigure>
</image>

<ol>
    <li>
        <p workspace="0.5in">
            <m>\sin(\theta)</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="0.5in">
            <m>\sin(\phi)</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="0.5in">
            <m>\tan(\theta)</m>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="0.5in">
            <m>\cos(\theta)</m>
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>

</sidebyside>

</paragraphs>

</page>

<page>

<paragraphs>
    <title>Applications of Right Triangle Trigonometry</title>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
            A <m>200</m> ft tall tower is to be anchored by cables that make a <m>30^{\circ}</m> angle with the ground. How long must the cables be and how far from the base of the tower must they be placed?
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <sidebyside>
        <p workspace="3in">
            A surveyor must measure the distance between two banks of a straight river. She sights a tree at the point <m>T</m> on the opposite bank of the river and drives a stake into the ground (at point <m>P</m>) directly across from the tree. The she walks <m>50</m> meters upstream and places a stake at the point <m>Q</m>. She measures then angle <m>\angle PQT</m> and finds that is it <m>50^{\circ}</m>. What is the width of the river?
        </p>   
        <image>   
<prefigure label = "river-problem" xmlns="https://prefigure.org">
<diagram dimensions="(300,300)" margins="(100,5,100,5)">
  <coordinates bbox="(-4,-2,8,10)">
    <definition>points=((5,0),(0,0),(5,8.6))</definition>
    <triangle vertices="points"
              labels="P,Q,T" show-vertices="yes"/>
    <angle-marker points="((5,8.6),(5,0),(0,0))" radius="30">
    </angle-marker>
    <angle-marker points="points" radius="30">
      <m>58^{\circ}</m>
    </angle-marker>
    <label anchor="(2.5,0)" alignment="south">
      <m>50</m>
    </label>
    <label anchor="(5,4.25)" alignment="east">
      <m>d</m>
    </label>
     <line p1="(0,8.6)" p2="(4,8.6)" dash="5 5 5" infinite="yes"/>
      <line p1="(0,0)" p2="(4,0)" dash="5 5 5" infinite="yes"/>
  </coordinates>
</diagram>
</prefigure>
</image>
        </sidebyside>
    </li>
</ol>
    
</paragraphs>

    
